This readme provides information about how to update and contribute to the bake documentation.


First things first:
*******************

The Bake documentation is wirtten in the .rst format and genrated using sphinx. 
(All necessary information about .rst can be found on the sphinx website)

    Some links:
    ***********

    * http://sphinx-doc.org/ 
    * http://openalea.gforge.inria.fr/doc/openalea/doc/_build/html/source/sphinx/rest_syntax.html


Basic Setup for writting and gernating the bake documenation
============================================================ 

* Install python 3.X (https://www.python.org/)
    * Do it they way of your choice  brew, package manager, windowws installer, you name it!

* Install Sphinx
    * I recomend installing sphinx using the python package management system (pip)
        * pip should be part of your python installation

    Example:
        $ pip3.4 install Sphinx

* Install the bootstrap theme
    * This also should be done using pip

    Example:
        $ pip3.4 install sphinx-bootstrap-theme



How to generate the Bake documentation
=======================================

1. Navigate to the documentation directory 

    Example:
        $ cd bake/documenation

2. generate the documenation

    Example:

        $ make html

3. Check out the documenation

    Docu can now be found in /bake/documenation/_build/html
